# Boiled Pork and Garlic Mud Sauce 

as seen http://www.eatingclubvancouver.com/2010/03/white-pork-with-garlic-sauce-two-ways.html 

## Ingredients

Garlic Sauce, Version 1
Makes about 3/4 cup

1/4 cup soy sauce
2 tablespoons finely chopped garlic
2 teaspoons sesame oil
1 tablespoon rice vinegar
1 tablespoon sugar
green onions, chopped
chili peppers, chopped

Combine all ingredients together. (Add your desired amount of green onions and chili peppers.)

Garlic Mud Sauce ("Go Crying to Your Mama If You Can't Handle the Garlic" Sauce)
Makes about 1 cup

1-2 heads garlic
6 tablespoons soy sauce
3 tablespoons white sugar
1-2 tablespoons brown sugar
2 tablespoons rice vinegar
